The paper deals with algorithmic aspects of graphs, specifically comparing and illustrating the use of graphs of bounded tree-width and graphs of bounded clique-width. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with graph theory and algorithms. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with algorithms for computing basic graph parameters. 

cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with polynomial time algorithms. 

cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper deals with graphs and their properties. 

cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a less likely sub-category, but possible as the paper deals with graph theory and its applications.
